[2]
Date: Fri 20 Aug 2010
Source: Yahoo News, Reuters report [abbreviated, edited]
<http://news.yahoo.com/s/nm/20100820/hl_nm/us_nigeria_cholera>


"Recent cholera cases are mainly from the northeastern part of the
country," said Dr Henry Akpan, head of epidemiology in Nigeria's
ministry of health, adding that 4665 cases had been recorded in
Africa's most populous nation since January [2010].

As well as cholera, Nigeria is also fighting a measles epidemic. The
disease, characterized by a high temperature and red spots on the
body, has killed more than 1400 people in Africa this year [2010] in
some of the most serious outbreaks seen for a decade. Health Minister
Onyebuchi Chukwu said Nigeria had confirmed 4771 cases in 2010, a
10-fold increase on the same period last year [2009]. He said
government would provide NGN 2.1 billion naira (USD 14 million) of
vaccines and syringes to combat the epidemic.

[Byline: Nick Tattersall]

