[ProMED-mail thanks Barry Dyer for drawing attention to this
information. In May 2010 the total for the whole of the African
continent was 64 00 cases of measles and 1100 deaths. These large and
deadly outbreaks of measles in 30 African countries threaten to
reverse gains made against the viral disease in the past 2 decades,
the World Health Organization (WHO) stated in May [2010].

More than 1100 deaths from measles have been reported among 64 000
known cases in Africa over the last year, with Nigeria, Chad, and
Zimbabwe having had the largest outbreaks. The preceding reports
quantify the current extent of the outbreak in Nigeria, but
information on the case/fatality ratio in Nigeria is lacking.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Nigeria is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/007*>. - Mod.CP]
